section.section:
The information required under paragraph (1) of this subsection shall include:
The frequency, severity, and potential long-term effects of pertussis;
Possible adverse reactions to pertussis vaccine which, if they occur, should be brought to the immediate attention of the health care provider;
A form listing symptoms to be monitored and containing places where information can be recorded to assist in reporting to the health care provider, local health officer, and the Department;
Measures parents should take to reduce the risk of, or to respond to, any major adverse reaction;
Early warning signs or symptoms to which parents should be alert as possible precursors to a major adverse reaction;
When and to whom parents should report any major adverse reaction;
A summary of the immunization requirements adopted under § 7-403(a) of the Education Article, including those related to pertussis vaccine; and
The information required under § 18-332(a)(1) through (3) of this subtitle.
